Other Functions

collapse

  • collapse(attrNames: string[], attributeArrays: number[][]): { itemSize: number; name: string; order: string[]; value: number[] }[]

  • Allow to collapse special attributes based on name suffixes

    • vector3: (x,y,z)
    • smatrix3: (xx, xy, xz, yy, yz, zz)
    • matrix3: (xx, xy, xz, yx, yy, yz, zx, zy, zz)
    As an example, if names includes 'Ux', 'Uy' and 'Uz', then all the tree attributes will be collapsed into one vector3 attribute (with itemSize=3) named 'U'
    example
    const attributes = [[5,6], [1,2], [3,4]]
const names = ['uz', 'ux', 'uy']
console.log( collapse(names, attributes) )

    will display

    {
  names: [ 'u' ],
  values: [ [ 1, 3, 5, 2, 4, 6 ] ],
  itemSizes: [ 3 ],
  orders: [ [ 'x', 'y', 'z' ] ]
}

    Parameters

    • attrNames: string[]

      The attribute names (array)

    • attributeArrays: number[][]

    Returns { itemSize: number; name: string; order: string[]; value: number[] }[]

    flat arrays of collapsed attributes

decodeXYZ

  • decodeXYZ(buffer: string, __namedParameters?: { merge?: boolean; shared?: boolean }): DataFrame[]

  • Format in order to know this is a cube:

    # nx: 10
# ny: 10
# nz: 10
# x y z attr1 attr2 ...
0 0 0  1 3
...
    example
    decodeXYZ(buffer)
decodeXYZ(buffer, {merge: false})
decodeXYZ(buffer, {merge: false, shared: false})

    Parameters

    • buffer: string
    • __namedParameters: { merge?: boolean; shared?: boolean } = ...
      • Optional merge?: boolean
      • Optional shared?: boolean

    Returns DataFrame[]
